@startuml multipath_resource_access
title Multipath Resource Access Architecture\nAlternative paths keep an IT resource reachable when one path fails

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam roundcorner 6
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #EAF2F8
  BorderColor #2874A6
}
skinparam node {
  BackgroundColor #FDEBD0
  BorderColor #B9770E
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #D5F5E3
  BorderColor #1E8449
}

node "Physical Server A" as ps {
  component "Multipathing System\n(server or hypervisor)" as mp
  component "HBA / Path 1" as p1
  component "HBA / Path 2" as p2
}

database "Cloud Storage Device\nLUN A" as lun

mp -down-> p1
mp -down-> p2

p1 -down-> lun : path 1 (active)
p2 -down-> lun : path 2 (active)

note right of mp
  (1) Two distinct paths to LUN A.
  (2) Without multipathing, each
      path appears as a different LUN.
  (3) Multipathing is configured.
  (4) LUN A is seen as one identical
      LUN from both paths.
  (5) Server has access via two paths.
  (6) A link failure occurs on one path.
  (7) Server keeps using LUN A via
      the remaining active path.
end note

note left of ps
  Supporting mechanisms:
  Cloud Storage Device, Hypervisor
  (redundant links to virtual servers),
  Logical Network Perimeter
  (privacy across paths),
  Resource Replication
  (alternative-path instances),
  Virtual Server.
end note

@enduml
